INGREDIENTS
2 (15 oz) cans black beans
1 bag vegetable slaw mix
4 cloves garlic
4 buns or rolls
1 medium yellow onion
3/4 to 1 cup BBQ sauce
1/2 cup vegan mayonnaise
2 tbsp apple cider vinegar or rice vinegar
1 tbsp Dijon mustard
1 tbsp pure maple syrup
1 tsp onion powder
2 tbsp extra virgin olive oil
 
DIRECTIONS
1 Peel and dice the onion and mince garlic.
2 Drain and rinse the beans in a colander.
3 In a large bowl, whisk together the mayonnaise, vinegar, Dijon, maple syrup, and onion powder. Add vegetable slaw mix and mix until well combined.
4 Preheat medium saucepan over medium heat. Once saucepan is hot, add oil and swirl to coat the bottom.
5 Add the onion and garlic to the saucepan; cook, stirring frequently, until slightly softened, 4-5 minutes.
6 Add black beans to the saucepan with the onion. Stir to combine.
7 Add BBQ Sauce ‚Äì I use somewhere between 3/4 and 1 cup. Stir to combine. Reduce heat to low and simmer, stirring occasionally, while you toast the buns. (You don‚Äôt want to add too much bc then it‚Äôs soupy)
8 Toast the buns (if desired)
9 To serve, place the bottom half of a bun on each plate. Top with bean mixture and some of the slaw; close with top half of the bun. Enjoy!

