Recipe (yields 2-3 servings)‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
Ingredients:‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
~ 1 pack of firm tofu, drained well‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
~ 1/4 cup chopped celery (used Chinese celery)‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
~ 1/4 cup chopped jicama‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
~ 1 small carrot, chopped‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
~ 2.5 tablespoons tapioca starch‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
~ 2 teaspoons salt‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
~ a pinch of white pepper‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
~ oil for pan-frying‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
~ Sweet chili sauce with chopped cilantro‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
‚úîÔ∏èMash tofu in a bowl, if it's too wet, use a paper towel to absorb moisture. Add celery, jicama, carrot, starch, salt & white pepper to tofu & mix until well combined. Take about 2 tablespoons of mixture & mold it into a patty by passing it between your palmsüôåüèª ‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£‚Å£
‚úîÔ∏èIn a heated non-stick pan, drizzle a thin layer of oil covering the pan, place patty in slowly one by one.‚Å£
‚úîÔ∏èUsing low-med heat, pan-fry cakes until golden brown on both sides. It's best to flip when the tofu starts to turn golden brown at the bottom. ‚Å£
*I place tofu cakes on a parchment paper while working on the rest. Parchment paper helps absorbs some moisture too.
‚Äã
‚ÄãTo serve, wrap tofu cakes with your favorite leafy greens & dip in sweet chili sauce with a squeeze of lime juice.‚Å£‚Å£
Note: chopped cilantro & sweet chili sauce is the best combo.
